      <hedline>
        <hl1>Despoiling Our Earth</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert E Griffin letter, commenting on Bob Herbert's July 10 Op-Ed article on global warming, says threat seems more of problem with human nature than with environment</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cold Facts of Global Warming,'' by Bob Herbert (column, July 10):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cold Facts of Global Warming,'' by Bob Herbert (column, July 10):</p>
        <p>The threat of global warming seems more of a problem with human nature than with the environment. For human beings to consume their heirs' habitat requires denial and rationalization. We are not able to admit to ourselves that our behavior is antisocial. There appears little hope for a species that seems so willing to sacrifice its offspring and commit collective suicide.</p>
        <p>ROBERT E. GRIFFIN  Forty Fort, Pa., July 10, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a psychologist.</p>
      </block>
